MID_支援_オボロ_リンカ_Ｃ: $t1$Wmオボロ|7$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E怒,|$w0|Now then... all that's left\nis to tidy up around here...$k\n$Wmリンカ|3$w0|$Wsリンカ|$WaAh... Oboro.\nWhat are you staring at?$k$pOh, it's your turn to bus\nthe tables today, isn't it?$k$pApologies, I'll get out of your way.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$Eキメ,|Hey, Rinka...\nCan you hold on a minute?$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E苦,|Wh-what is it...?$k\n$Wsオボロ|$WaYour eating...\nWell, the way you eat is rather messy.$k$pIt ends up being a real pain to clean.$k$pCould you perhaps try to be\na little tidier when you're eating?$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E怒,|Tidier...?\nWhat do you mean?$k\n$Wsオボロ|$WaI'm talking about gravy spilled on the table\nand scraps of food littering the floor!$k\n$Wsリンカ|$WaAh... I get what you're saying.$k$pIn the Flame Tribe, we eat with our hands.\nTo us, it's honorable to enjoy a hearty meal.$k$pI'm getting used to your dining customs...\nI've been advised to give chopsticks a try,$k$pbut I'm not used to handling them at all.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E苦,|I see... Table manners vary among\ndifferent groups, don't they?$k$pBut if I have to clean up every time\nyou make a mess, it's going to be a pain...$k$p$E怒,|Here's the deal.\nI'll teach you how to use chopsticks.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E苦,|Wh-what?!$k$pNo... There's no need for that...$k\n$Wsオボロ|$WaWell, are you going to start picking\nup after yourself when you eat?$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E通常,|Not going to happen.\nIt's just not my style.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E怒,汗|Well that's too bad.\nThis isn't your Flame Tribe's village.$k$pWhen you belong to a group, you agree to\nfollow their rules and customs, do you not?$k$pI'll be teaching you as best I can,\nso be ready for it the next time we meet.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wd$w0|$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E苦,|Be ready for it...?\nUghhh... So aggravating...$k
MID_支援_オボロ_リンカ_Ｂ: $t1$Wmオボロ|7$Wmリンカ|3$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E怒,|$w0|Right, don't hold chopsticks\nwith your entire hand.$k$pLightly hold them between your\nindex, middle, and ring fingers.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E苦,|Argh...!$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E通常,|Apply pressure with your middle finger.\nIt's easier on your hand that way.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E怒,汗|B-but...\nSuch an unnatural thing... to do...$k$p...Oh, it broke.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E苦,|Yeah...\nThis is the... fifth pair you've broken.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E怒,|Like I said, it's too difficult for me.\nHow many times do I need to tell you?$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E怒,|You can't give up yet.\nJust think how useful chopsticks can be.$k$pEven the fish you love would\nbe so much tidier to eat.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$Eキメ,|Or you could grab the fish, eat it,\nand spit out the bones afterward.$k$pIf you feel like it, just chew up\nthe bones and eat those, too!$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E苦,|Uh-huh...\nThat's why your eating leaves such a mess.$k$p$E怒,|Rinka, you ready?\nTo neatly eat a fish is to eat its whole body.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E通常,|Hm...?$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E怒,汗|Up until now, you haven't\nbeen eating the entire body.$k$pThanks to your aggressive eating habits,\nyou're leaving perfectly good food behind.$k$p$E通常,|So much leftover food going to waste.\nYou're not okay with that, are you, Rinka?$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E怒,|I... I'm leaving food behind?!$k$pNghh... \nI'm sure...$k$pThe fact that I could leave behind food...\nThat's unacceptable...!$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E通常,|Actually, tonight's meal was grilled fish.\nWatch how I eat it.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E通常,|A-ah...$k\n$Wc$Sbv40|1000|$Fo1000|$Sbv100|1000|$Fi1000|$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E怒,汗|Aaah...!$k$pTh-this is... I can't believe it.\nThe fish is just skin and bones...!$k$pOboro, the way you ate that fish,\nyou make it look like an art form...!$k\n$Wsオボロ|$WaIf you can learn to use chopsticks,\nyou can eat as neatly as this.$k$pEven better, no bones go flying,\nand the dishes and tablecloth stay clean.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$Eキメ,|I see...\nSo that's why chopsticks are so useful.$k$pAlright, Oboro.\nRun me through the process again!$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E笑,|I'd be glad to.$k
MID_支援_オボロ_リンカ_Ａ: $t1$Wmオボロ|7$Wmリンカ|3$Wsリンカ|$Wa$Eキメ,|$w0|Take a look, Oboro!\nNothing on this fish but skin and bones!$k$pAnd this tablecloth!\nNot a single stain, either!$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E笑,|How awesome is that, Rinka?$k$pThe rest of the room is free of debris,\nso I'd say you're handling chopsticks well.$k$pWith these new skills, your eating\nhas become much less messy.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E笑,|Indeed, and it's all thanks to you, Oboro.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E通常,|Not in the least.\nIt's all thanks to your stunning effort.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E通常,|Still, the feeling I get from\neating an entire dish like this...$k$pIt goes beyond the simple satisfaction\nof filling yourself with a good feast.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E怒,|Yeah, that's right.\nFinishing an entire meal...$k$pIt shows gratitude for the chef's cooking, \nand respect for the land from which it came.$k$p$E通常,|At least, that's what I believe.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$WaI see...\nSo that is the custom of Hoshido.$k$pI'm going to study even more.$k$pOboro, I want to tear down our cultural\nbarriers and understand more of your ways.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E笑,|Yeah, that's the spirit.$k$pFrom now on, let's try to bridge\nthe gap between each other.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E笑,|Yeah!$k$pIn return, I'll teach you how the\nFlame Tribe eats their meals.$k$pBut since you already cleaned up...\nLet's try deep-mountain hunting first.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E通常,|Sure! Thanks.$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E通常,|Our eating traditions are wonderful, yeah?\nDigging into the hearty meat of a fresh kill,$k$pflesh and blood flying about,\nis our way of honoring its life.$k\n$Wsオボロ|$Wa$E通常,汗|Yeah... When we do this, my clothes\nare going to be a mess, huh?$k\n$Wsリンカ|$Wa$E笑,|Yep, and you're going to love it!$k
